#- "Why haven't you moved out yet?" Itaqi would say. "You literally can't live here." He would shout. Konvexen was, frankly, getting tired of it.

"I'm going to get the paper." Konvexen belted.

"Don't come back." 
#- Itaqi replied.

Konvexen stepped into his minecart and teleported out of his obsidian den. There, he waled out from the vast, abysmal emptiness that is the Defiance Towers and toward the gate. After openning it and looking around, protecting 
#- himself from the wind with his robe, he came to realize that no newspaper is, or ever has been, delivered in Orion. He began to shut the gate when he saw, just one house over, a petite girl in a purple outfit talking to his neighbor, Silverwill_JDK. 
